.SH NAME
Bitcoin::Crypto::PSBT::Field \- Single field of a PSBT
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 1
\&        use Bitcoin::Crypto::PSBT::Field;
\&
\&        my $field = Bitcoin::Crypto::PSBT::Field\->new(
\&                type => \*(AqPSBT_IN_OUTPUT_INDEX\*(Aq,
\&                value => 1,
\&        );
\&
\&        $psbt\->add_field($field, 1);
.Ve
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
This is a helper class which represents a single PSBT field.
.PP
While fields hold bytestring data, Bitcoin::Crypto defines some serializers and
deserializers to make it easier to handle the keys and values. These try to
DWIM and should be pretty straightforward, for example
\&\f(CW\*(C`PSBT_GLOBAL_UNSIGNED_TX\*(C'\fR deserializes into an object of
Bitcoin::Crypto::Transaction. Serializers are not currently documented, but
fields \f(CW\*(C`key_data\*(C'\fR and \f(CW\*(C`value_data\*(C'\fR of Bitcoin::Crypto::PSBT::FieldType
holds the descriptions of what is the type after deserialization (and before
serialization). Reading the source of Bitcoin::Crypto::PSBT::FieldType may
be required if it isn\*(Aqt clear how they are implemented for a specific field.
.PP
Reading the value through "raw_value" will return a bytestring, but reading
through \f(CW\*(C`value\*(C'\fR will use the deserializer. Calling \f(CW\*(C`set_value\*(C'\fR will use the
serializer to update "raw_value". The field only holds raw data and uses
serializers to update it as a convenience.
.SH INTERFACE
.IX Header "INTERFACE"
.SS Attributes
.IX Subsection "Attributes"
\fImap\fR
.IX Subsection "map"
.PP
The Bitcoin::Crypto::PSBT::Map object this field belongs to. Field can only
belong to a single map at a time. There is no need to set it manually, it will
be set when adding the field to a map.
.PP
\&\fIwriter:\fR \f(CW\*(C`set_map\*(C'\fR
.PP
\fItype\fR
.IX Subsection "type"
.PP
\&\fBRequired in the constructor\fR. The type of the field. Must be an instance of
Bitcoin::Crypto::PSBT::FieldType. Can be coerced from a \f(CW\*(C`PSBT_*\*(C'\fR field name.
.PP
\fIraw_key\fR
.IX Subsection "raw_key"
.PP
\&\fBAvailable in the constructor\fR. Raw bytestring keydata for this field. Only
valid for field types which actually define key data.
.PP
To use a dedicated serializer for a key, use \f(CW\*(C`key\*(C'\fR (constructor key), \f(CW\*(C`key\*(C'\fR
(reader method) or \f(CW\*(C`set_key\*(C'\fR (writer method).
.PP
\&\fIwriter:\fR \f(CW\*(C`set_raw_key\*(C'\fR
.PP
\fIraw_value\fR
.IX Subsection "raw_value"
.PP
\&\fBAvailable in the constructor\fR. Raw bytestring valuedata for this field.
.PP
To use a dedicated serializer for a value, use \f(CW\*(C`value\*(C'\fR (constructor key), \f(CW\*(C`value\*(C'\fR
(reader method) or \f(CW\*(C`set_value\*(C'\fR (writer method).
.PP
\&\fIwriter:\fR \f(CW\*(C`set_raw_value\*(C'\fR
